Description: The GeoNames Ontology makes it possible to add geospatial semantic information to the Word Wide Web. All over 6.2 million geonames toponyms now have a unique URL with a corresponding RDF web service. Other services describe the relation between toponyms.SPARQL endpoints for this data are made available by third parties. [Geonames at Kasabi](http://kasabi.com/dataset/geonames/)- and [FactForge](http://factforge.net/sparql) has it loaded as well.
